FT  25 MAR 94 / International Capital Markets: Austrian group in global
issue
Mayr Melnhof Karton, the Austrian packaging group, expects to raise Sch3bn
when it issues equity next month as part of its initial flotation, Reuter
reports from Vienna.
The group, Europe's number two cardboard packaging maker, is to offer 4m
shares from April 19. One third of the proceeds is to be used to increase
capacity, with the balance used for funding acquisitions, the company said.
Morgan Stanley International, which is placing the international tranche,
expects turnover of Sch8.7bn this year. Pre-tax profits are expected to
total Sch210m, rising to Sch436m next year.
